node.title: Adelaide Crows AFLW player moved to inactive list after refusing to be vaccinated
node.description: The Adelaide Crows has placed Deni Varnhagen on the club's inactive list because she is refusing to get vaccinated against COVID-19.
node.content: ["The Adelaide Crows have placed AFLW defender Deni Varnhagen on the club's inactive list because she is refusing to be vaccinated against COVID-19.", "Under AFL rules, all players and football staff must receive the first vaccination by November 19 and must be fully vaccinated by December 17.", "Varnhagen, who is also a nurse, was among dozens of people who rallied in Adelaide on Tuesday to protest against mandatory vaccination.", "Hospital workers in South Australia are also required to be vaccinated under a health order which came into effect this week.", "More to come."]
